entry.title: First Post
entry.summary:
Image Features Extraction Package¶

package doc: https://rempic.github.io/Image-Features-Extraction/¶

Tutorial¶

This Python package allows the fast extraction and classification of features from a set of images. The resulting data frame can be used as training and testing set for machine learning classifier.

This package was originally developed to extract measurements of single cell nuclei from microscopy images (see figure above). The package can be used to extract features from any set of images for a variety of applications. Below it is shown a map of Boston used for city density and demographic models.

<h1 id="Image-Features-Extraction-Package">Image Features Extraction Package<a class="anchor-link" href="#Image-Features-Extraction-Package">¶</a></h1><h2 id="package-doc:-https://rempic.github.io/Image-Features-Extraction/">package doc: <a href="https://rempic.github.io/Image-Features-Extraction/">https://rempic.github.io/Image-Features-Extraction/</a><a class="anchor-link" href="#package-doc:-https://rempic.github.io/Image-Features-Extraction/">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Tutorial">Tutorial<a class="anchor-link" href="#Tutorial">¶</a></h2><p>This Python package allows the fast extraction and classification of features from a set of images. The resulting data frame can be used as training and testing set for machine learning classifier.</p>
<p><img src="1.png" /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>This package was originally developed to extract measurements of single cell nuclei from microscopy images (see figure above). The package can be used to extract features from any set of images for a variety of applications.
Below it is shown a map of Boston used for city density and demographic models.</p>
<p><img src="12.png" /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [1]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span> <span class="n">matplotlib</span> <span class="n">inline</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">image_features_extraction.Images</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">fe</span>


<span class="n">IMGS</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'../images/REMI'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_name</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">IMG_POINTS</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">#IMG_POINTS.set_image_intensity(IMG_8BIT)</span>

<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">))</span>

<h2 id="Features-extraction-for-spatial-classification-of-images">Features extraction for spatial classification of images<a class="anchor-link" href="#Features-extraction-for-spatial-classification-of-images">¶</a></h2><p>The image below shows a possible workflow for image feature extraction: two sets of images with different classification labels are used to produce two data sets for training and testing a classifier</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="An-example-of-Collection-object-and-Iterator-implementation">An example of Collection-object and Iterator implementation<a class="anchor-link" href="#An-example-of-Collection-object-and-Iterator-implementation">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p><img src="4b.png" /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The object 'Image' includes the function Voronoi(), which returns the object Voronoi of my package Voronoi_Features.
The Voronoi object can be used to measure the voronoi tassels of each image regions. It includes >30 measurements.
Below an example of voronoi diagrams from the image shown above</p>
<p><img src="09.png" /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p><img src="voro3.png" /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Image-features-extraction-for-city-density-and-demographic-analysis-modelling">Image features extraction for city density and demographic analysis modelling<a class="anchor-link" href="#Image-features-extraction-for-city-density-and-demographic-analysis-modelling">¶</a></h2><p>Create the Images root object and laod the images contained in the folder</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [10]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span> <span class="n">matplotlib</span> <span class="n">inline</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">image_features_extraction.Images</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">fe</span>


<span class="n">IMGS</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'../images/CITY'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">IMG</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_name</span><span class="p">())</span>


<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">imshow</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_image_segmentation</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="To-measure-intensity-from-image-regions">To measure intensity from image regions<a class="anchor-link" href="#To-measure-intensity-from-image-regions">¶</a></h2><p>The example below shows how to associate a grayscale image to a binary one for intensity measurement. The package uses intenally a very simple segmentation algorithm based on an Otsu Thresholding method for segmentation of binary images. The goal of the package in not to segment images but to measurement their segmented features. The corect way to use this package is by using as input pre-segmented binary images and if intensity measurement are needed you can assaciate the original grayscale image.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [8]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">IMG</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">IMG</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_image_intensity</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="n">features</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMG</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'label'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'area'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'perimeter'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'centroid'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'moments'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'mean_intensity'</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">features</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>
</div>

<span class="n">storage_name</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'../images/DB1.csv'</span>

<h2 id="Extract-and-save-cellular-features">Extract and save cellular features<a class="anchor-link" href="#Extract-and-save-cellular-features">¶</a></h2><h4 id="run-twice-to-extract-CENT>2-and-CTRL-features:-first-add-'CT'-and-after-'CA'-to-EXP_COND">run twice to extract CENT>2 and CTRL features: first add 'CT' and after 'CA' to EXP_COND<a class="anchor-link" href="#run-twice-to-extract-CENT>2-and-CTRL-features:-first-add-'CT'-and-after-'CA'-to-EXP_COND">¶</a></h4>
</div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [26]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span> <span class="n">matplotlib</span> <span class="n">inline</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">image_features_extraction.Images</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">fe</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>

<span class="n">EXP_COND</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'CT'</span>

<span class="n">IMGS_BIN</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1">/bin'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">EXP_COND</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">IMGS_SMAD</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1">/smad'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">EXP_COND</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">IMGS_YAP</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1">/yap'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">EXP_COND</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">IMGS_DNA</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fe</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Images</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1">/dna'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">EXP_COND</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_names</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS_SMAD</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_names</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS_YAP</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_names</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMGS_DNA</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">file_names</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="features-for-nuclear-and-voronoi">features for nuclear and voronoi<a class="anchor-link" href="#features-for-nuclear-and-voronoi">¶</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [29]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">IMG_BIN</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMGS_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1">#A1.set_image_intensity(IMGS_SMAD.item(0))</span>
<span class="n">VORO</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Voronoi</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_NUCL</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'area'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'perimeter'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'centroid'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'minor_axis_length'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'major_axis_length'</span><span class="p">,</span> \
                        <span class="s1">'eccentricity'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'extent'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'equivalent_diameter'</span><span class="p">,</span>\
                        <span class="s1">'solidity'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'nucl_'</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="n">FEATURES_VORO</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">VORO</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'area'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'perimeter'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'centroid'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'minor_axis_length'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'major_axis_length'</span><span class="p">,</span> \
                        <span class="s1">'eccentricity'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'extent'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'equivalent_diameter'</span><span class="p">,</span>\
                        <span class="s1">'solidity'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'voro_'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_NUCL</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FEATURES_VORO</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="nucl-voro-centroid-distance">nucl voro centroid distance<a class="anchor-link" href="#nucl-voro-centroid-distance">¶</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [30]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># ADD SMAD ACTIVATION </span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">xn</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_centroid</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">yn</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_centroid</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">xv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_centroid</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">yv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_centroid</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">centr_dist</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">xn</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">xv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">yn</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">yv</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_feature</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'nucl_voro_centroid_distance'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">centr_dist</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="proteins-intensity">proteins intensity<a class="anchor-link" href="#proteins-intensity">¶</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [32]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">NUCL_PROT_INTENSITY</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">IMG_8BIT</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'protein'</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="c1"># NUCLER INTENSITY OF DIFFERENT PROTEINS</span>
    <span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_image_intensity</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG_8BIT</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">VORO</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Voronoi</span><span class="p">()</span>
    
    <span class="n">pref_nucl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'nucl_'</span><span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">prefix</span> <span class="o">+</span><span class="s1">'_'</span>
    <span class="n">pref_voro</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'voro_'</span><span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">prefix</span> <span class="o">+</span><span class="s1">'_'</span>
    
    <span class="n">FEATURES_NUCL</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'intensity_image'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'mean_intensity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'max_intensity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'min_intensity'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">pref_nucl</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">FEATURES_VORO</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">VORO</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'intensity_image'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'mean_intensity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'max_intensity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'min_intensity'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">pref_voro</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_NUCL</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FEATURES_VORO</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [33]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">FEATURES_SMAD</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">NUCL_PROT_INTENSITY</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">IMGS_SMAD</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'smad'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_YAP</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">NUCL_PROT_INTENSITY</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">IMGS_YAP</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'yap'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_DNA</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">NUCL_PROT_INTENSITY</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">IMG_BIN</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">IMGS_DNA</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">prefix</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'dna'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="add-ratio-cyto/nucl-intensity-(protein-activity)">add ratio cyto/nucl intensity (protein activity)<a class="anchor-link" href="#add-ratio-cyto/nucl-intensity-(protein-activity)">¶</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [34]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># ADD SMAD ACTIVATION </span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_SMAD</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">df_main</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">In</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">I</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">I</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_smad_intensity_image</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">Iv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">I</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">I</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_smad_intensity_image</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">voro_mean_intensity_nonucl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Iv</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">In</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_main</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_area</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">df_main</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_area</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">activity</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_smad_mean_intensity</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">voro_mean_intensity_nonucl</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_SMAD</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_feature</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'nucl_smad_activity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">activity</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="c1"># ADD YAP ACTIVATION </span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_YAP</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">df_main</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dataframe</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">In</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">I</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">I</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_yap_intensity_image</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">Iv</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">I</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">I</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_yap_intensity_image</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">voro_mean_intensity_nonucl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Iv</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">In</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_main</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_area</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">df_main</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_area</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">activity</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nucl_yap_mean_intensity</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">voro_mean_intensity_nonucl</span>

<span class="n">FEATURES_YAP</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_feature</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'nucl_yap_activity'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">activity</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [35]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">FEATURES_FINAL</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_MAIN</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FEATURES_SMAD</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">FEATURES_FINAL</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FEATURES_FINAL</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FEATURES_YAP</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># ADD FEATURE: FILE_NAME</span>

<span class="c1"># ADD FEATURE: EXP_COND</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">scipy.stats</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">binned_statistic</span>

<span class="c1"># BINNIG</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voro_area</span>
